I really enjoy reading tips like this. The mnemonic I use for looping over multi-dimensional arrays in C is: the right-most index should be the inner-most loop:<p><pre><code>    for (i = 0; i < M; i++) {
        for (j = 0; j < N; j++) {
            x[i][j] = ...;
        }
    }</code></pre>
